1297  - If this state is a consistent state with a default action, then
1298  the only way this function was invoked is if the default action
1299  is an error action. In that case, don't check for expected
1300  tokens because there are none.

1302  this state is a consistent state with a default action. Thus,
1303  detecting the absence of a lookahead is sufficient to determine
1304  that there is no unexpected or expected token to report. In that
1305  case, just report a simple "syntax error".
1306  - Don't assume there isn't a lookahead just because this state is a
1307  consistent state with a default action. There might have been a
1308  previous inconsistent state, consistent state with a non-default
1309  action, or user semantic action that manipulated yychar.
1310  - Of course, the expected token list depends on states to have
1311  correct lookahead information, and it depends on the parser not
1312  to perform extra reductions after fetching a lookahead from the
1313  scanner and before detecting a syntax error. Thus, state merging
1314  (from LALR or IELR) and default reductions corrupt the expected
1315  token list. However, the list is correct for canonical LR with
1316  one exception: it will still contain any token that will not be
1317  accepted due to an error action in a later state.
1318  */
